title: Mill Ceek Circuit
description:
Mill Creek Circuit
One mile loop in beautiful Mill Creek Park, Youngstown Ohio
Sunday, May 22, 2011 Held under U. S. Cycling Federation permit ID # pending
course: Race course: Just a rolling one mile loop with a fast descent and sweeping right turn to a 0.1 mile climb before the start/finish. The entire course will be swept clean the day of the race for you to challange yourself and other racers. The course is closed to traffic.
registration: The registration area is adjacent the parking lot and the course is accessible by foot or bike only a short distance over the hill.
notes:
Location of race: Mill Creek Park. James L. Wick Recreation Area. Entry Fee: $25.00
Max of $499 prize list for any race
directions: Directions: From the North and West Take I-680 South exiting at 3-B (Belle Vista Ave.) At the first stop sign turn left on Manhattan. Turn right at the next stop sign on Belle Vista Ave heading south into the park. From the South and East Take I-680 North to Exit 3C. At the first stop sign turn left onto Wellington Avenue. At the first stop light turn left on Belle Vista Avenue heading south into the park.

Madeira Centennial Criterium
course: The 1 mile course dives in and out of the local streets that make up the central Madeira business district.  Start heading north on Miami, 180 back down to south on Miami, straight until the 180 by Coffee Please, right on Railroad, left on Laurel, then the final right on Miami and 175 meters to the finish at PNC Bank.   Two wide 180 degree  turns are featured at either end of the 1 mile circuit.
registration: Pre-registration is encouraged and can be completed here on BikeReg, or at BioWheels bike shop in Madeira.  Registration on race day is available for an additional $10.  Race day registration closes 30 minutes prior to posted start times.  Staging for events will be done by order of registration.
notes: The Madeira Centennial Race Committee is pleased to announce continuation of the first-ever bike race held in the heart of Madeira:  The Madeira Centennial Criterium, Friday,  June 24th 2011. All categories of criterium racers will be competing from 5pm – 9:30pm.  Complete with music, food, beer tent, and kids events.  Cyclists will battle for over $5500 in cash and merchandise.  Fun for all!
directions:
From Columbus I-71 South, take the Montgomery Rd exit 12.  Turn left on Montgomery Rd.  Turn right on Hosbrook.  At dead end, turn left on Euclid.  Parking will be off of Euclid as you reach Madeira, look for parking signage.

From downtown Cincinnati to I-71 North, take the Kenwood Rd exit 11.  Right turn on Kenwood.  First left turn on Euclid.  Parking will be off of Euclid as you reach Madeira, look for parking signage.

title: Hyde Park Blast Criterium
description:
The Hyde Park Blast cycling races are the largest one day competitve cycling event in Ohio, Kentucky and Indiana.  The 2010 race had more than 350 cyclists registered from 27 states with competitors from Canada and South America. 
The Blast cycling races are some of the most anticipated cycling races for both junior level cyclists and professionals of national standing. The feature Pro 1-2 race is part of the USA CRITS Series and finishes under the lights in front of our large, supportive crowd.
course: The Hyde Park Blast features the components that make criterium cycling racing an American legacy: the course is challenging and showcases one of Cincinnati’s most historic entertainment and retail districts; the large crowds come for the fun of the day-long event; and, the large crowd and broad community support make the Hyde Park Blast a strong marketing opportunity for our sponsors.  This is a four-corner criterium with 1 left and 3 right hand technical turns. The course is relatively flat with one short hill. Hyde Park Square is a great place to participate or spectate. Be sure to stay for the Block Party for food, music and fun! It begins at 6pm!
directions:
From Columbus: take I-71 South to Exit 5 Dana Ave.  Turn left onto Dana.  Follow Dana and continue straight onto Observatory Ave.  Follow Observatory and turn left on Paxton.  Team parking is at the corner of Paxton and Erie Ave.

From Lexington:  Take I-75 North through downtown Cincinnati and exit at Dana Ave.  Turn left at Duck Creek Rd.  Follow Duck Creek to Dana Ave and veer right on Dana Ave.  Follow Dana and continue straight onto Observatory Ave.  Follow Observatory and turn left on Paxton.  Team parking is at the corner of Paxton and Erie Ave.

title: JONES Racing Junior Criterium
description:
Juniors Only Criterium presented by J.O.N.E.S (Juniors of Ohio NorthEast) Racing. 
EVENT DATE: Saturday, August 13, 2011
“Lance Armstrong Junior Race Series” application pending
course:
Entirely closed paved .6 mile loop course is located at The Chapel - Green Campus.   The Chapel is located just off I-77 between Akron and Canton.    

For spectators: Park-like setting. The Chapel offers a 1.2-mile walking trail as well as two softball fields and a soccer field.
registration:
Register online or in person. 
In-person registration opens at the parking lot of The Chapel at 1:20pm.  Registration closes 10 minutes before the start of each age-group start time.   
USA Cycling annual or one-day license required for all participants.
Riders can enter more than one event by paying the additional entry fee.  2nd/3rd/4th race is only $10. 
Riders can \"race up\" in junior age graded categories. 
example - 11 year old can race in the 10-12 category and also race up into the 13-14/15-16/or 17-18 categories by paying the additional $10 race fee.
Official racing age is determined as of 12/31/2011.
Approved helmets are required. 
All races are run under USA Cycling rules.  
All bicycles are subject to roll-out procedures for junior gearing.  Blocked gears can be used.
notes:
Awards: Awards for boys and girls in each age category.  Lance Armstrong Junior Race Series Medals to 1-3rd places*(pending USA Cycling approval). 
** Athletes ages 14 to 18 will have the opportunity to qualify for USA Cycling Regional Camps by finishing in the top five places in each LAJRS race. 

Racers in the Cat 3-4-5 race will be scored separately for upgrade points.   Awards in the Cat 3-4-5 race are 1st-3rd overall only, Male & Female. 

The Smith\'s Milk Road Race in Orrville is the following day so come for the weekend!
directions:
How Do I Get To the race site at The Chapel - Green Campus?

Coming from the North headed South on I-77
Exit onto the Massillon Road exit. Turn left on Massillon. At the second light, turn right onto Raber Road. The Chapel is 1/4 mile down Raber Road, on the right.

Coming from the South headed North on I-77
Exit onto the Massillon Road exit. Turn right on Massillon. At the first light, turn right onto Raber Road. The Chapel is 1/4 mile down Raber Road, on the right.

Akron-Canton (CAK) Airport and many economical hotels are located within 5-10 minutes of the race site.  

Link to maps. http://www.the-chapel.org/campuses/green

title: Milford Sunflower Classic
description: The road racing season wraps up with some of the best regional bicycle racers hitting the friendly streets of Old Milford for a total Prize Purse of $2000.  This rare Friday evening crit will end under the lights with plenty of live music, food and beverages for all kinds.
course: The course is a .8-mile loop with 5 corners, generally flat, with a small incline on the south end.
registration: Online registration is available at USACycling.org.  Online registration will close at 11:59 PM EST on Thursday, September 8, 2011.  Pre-registration is highly encouraged.  A $10 late fee will be assessed to all day of event registrations.  Onsite registration and check in will be at Bishop’s Bicycles at 313 Main Street, Milford, Ohio 45150 and will open at 5 PM on race day and close 15 minutes before each race.
notes: Riders will be able to warm up on the Little Miami Scenic Trail just 3 blocks from the start/finish line.
directions: Parking is available at Riverside Park on Water Street in Milford.

title: John Bryan Cyclocross Classic
course: Course: A 7 minute (A Men standard) course over the front face of the park. This year we will have wide open and fast sweeping turns, with a mix of gravel roads (100 meters), lots of grass, and a short section of singletrack. And of course...the YURT OF PAIN will be back this year!
registration:
Registration: Registration opens at 8:30am! There is a $10 late fee--day of registration--as per OVCX rules...so register early at BikeReg.com. JUST like last year, I will refund entrance fees for anyone who registers via BikeReg but then cannot make the race. We need the pre-reg to get registration setup and running smoothly, to assign bib-numbers, to make the race lists as complete as possible, and to have some operating capital before the race so my kids don\'t go hungry the month before--and our race is right after Thanksgiving, so if you don\'t register early I\'ll have to take the cash out of my checking acocunt and my 4 year old and 2 year old won\'t get any turkey! (I\'m actually not kidding, it\'s expensive to run a race with all the up-front costs and I don\'t make much on an Air Force salary.) So please register if there is even a SLIGHT chance you will race, and if you can\'t make it I\'ll send you a check...see, nothing to lose!

 
Military Discount--Anyone in our Armed Forces who presents their CAC card at registration gets $10 off.  Register on BikeReg at the full price and I\'ll hand you a 10 spot at the race.
notes: STAGING: We will be staging EVERY race in the series. It will work like this...the first 3 riders in the OVCX series, a promoter\'s discretion call-up, and then IN ORDER OF REGISTRATION down to the last rider! Just in case anyone needed any more motivation to sign up early at BikeReg. So the first row of every race is already spoken for...but the second row on back goes to everyone IN ORDER OF REGISTRATION! So sign up now!!!
directions:
Directions to Course:
FROM CINCINNATI & South: Take 75 North to I-675 North. Exit I-675 at Exit 20, and head east (right hand turn at the exit) on Dayton-Yellow Springs Road. Travel approximately 5 miles to the town of Yellow Springs. Go through the only traffic light on Dayton-Yellow Spring Road, and proceed to the next stop sign. Turn left on 68 North, and take first right hand turn at the traffic light onto Rt 343. Proceed to the next right hand turn, and turn onto Rt 370. John Bryan State Park is 1 mile down on the left hand side.

Proceed to the next right hand turn, and turn onto Rt 370. John Bryan State Park is 1 mile down on the left hand side. 

FROM the West: Take I-70 East until I-675 South. Take I-675 South until Exit 20, and head east (right hand turn at the exit) on Dayton-Yellow Springs Road. Travel approximately 5 miles to the town of Yellow Springs. Go through the only traffic light on Dayton-Yellow Spring Road, and proceed to the next stop sign. Turn left on 68 North, and take first right hand turn at the traffic light onto Rt 343. Proceed to the next right hand turn, and turn onto Rt 370. John Bryan State Park is 1 mile down on the left hand side.
